WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.680
Map region clickable blank.

00:00:03.680 --> 00:00:05.920
Map region clickable blank.

00:00:05.920 --> 00:00:10.480
Sadly, this is the experience
for blind people when they visit 99.9%

00:00:10.480 --> 00:00:13.480
of the over 30 million maps
on apps and websites today.

00:00:16.000 --> 00:00:17.480
In a world where maps

00:00:17.480 --> 00:00:21.040
touch every aspect of our lives,
from telling us where to go

00:00:21.360 --> 00:00:25.760
to showing the information around us,
there are those who are often left out.

00:00:25.960 --> 00:00:27.840
But what if there was a way
to make digital

00:00:27.840 --> 00:00:31.440
geographic information
inclusive and intuitive for everyone?

00:00:31.640 --> 00:00:35.440
Introducing Audiom, the world's first
inclusive digital,

00:00:35.440 --> 00:00:39.000
visual, auditory
and tactile map viewer and editor.

00:00:39.680 --> 00:00:42.760
With Audiom, maps
become interactive and user friendly.

00:00:43.160 --> 00:00:47.040
Zoom, adjust contrast, and customize
the map to work for you.

00:00:47.480 --> 00:00:51.000
Explore spaces and investigate data
with the only Web

00:00:51.000 --> 00:00:52.960
Content Accessibility Guidelines

00:00:52.960 --> 00:00:54.520
Triple-A compliant map.

00:00:54.520 --> 00:00:58.000
The unique non-visual Audiom experience
is similar to a video game,

00:00:58.560 --> 00:00:59.920
where users move a character

00:00:59.920 --> 00:01:03.960
around the map using their arrow keys
or other controller.

00:01:03.960 --> 00:01:07.440
Audiom can be added to a website or app
in just three simple steps.

00:01:08.000 --> 00:01:10.640
A customer gives us their geographic data.

00:01:10.640 --> 00:01:14.000
We process that geographic data
into something Audiom can use.

00:01:14.840 --> 00:01:17.040
And finally,
we provide a few lines of code

00:01:17.040 --> 00:01:20.920
that can be used to completely replace
or supplement an existing map.

00:01:21.040 --> 00:01:25.000
Join us in creating a world
where every map is accessible to everyone.

00:01:29.560 --> 00:01:31.560
? Outro instrumental music.
